    "discriminators": [
     "Hand-powered by definition: a rake, hoe or shovel is gritty friction against soil and gravel plus sparse metal clanks. It must NOT contain a sustained motor bed — that would be TOOLPowr or a MACHINES-GARDEN machine.",
     "No DSP separates a rake from a broom, or a garden hand tool from a workshop hand tool. This is a use-context label; TOOLHand is the same physics indoors. Text decides.",
     "Powered garden machines go to MACHINES-GARDEN per the explanation, and non-tool garden objects to OBJECTS-GARDEN."
