    "discriminators": [
     "A motor is a stable pitched drone: high harmonicity, low spectral_flatness, low crest factor, sustained for seconds. Drills and sanders spin up and down, so the pitch slope swings hard at the ends while the middle stays stationary.",
     "Against TOOLPneu: harmonic versus noisy. An electric drill whines; an air ratchet rattles and hisses. harmonicity and spectral_flatness invert between them — the cleanest separation in this category.",
     "Against TOOLHand: the sustained tonal bed is exactly what a hand tool cannot have.",
     "A circular saw biting into wood adds a bright screaming friction layer on top of the motor whine; the motor bed underneath still holds."
